ğŸŸ  Section 2: DAX & Modeling Logic
ğŸ”¹ 6. What is the difference between CALCULATE() and FILTER()?
Theory:
	â€¢ CALCULATE() changes context
	â€¢ FILTER() returns a table Example:
DAX
CALCULATE(SUM([Amount]), FILTER(Transactions, Transactions[Channel] = "UPI"))
ğŸ”¹ 7. How do you calculate year-over-year growth?
Code:
DAX
YoY = 
DIVIDE(
    [This Year] - [Last Year],
    [Last Year]
)
ğŸ”¹ 8. How do you create a dynamic measure based on slicer selection?
Code:
DAX
SelectedMetric = 
SWITCH(
    SELECTEDVALUE(Metric[Name]),
    "Total Spend", SUM(Transactions[Amount]),
    "Txn Count", COUNT(Transactions[TxnID])
)
ğŸ”¹ 9. How do you calculate running total?
Code:
DAX
RunningTotal = 
CALCULATE(
    SUM(Transactions[Amount]),
    FILTER(
        ALLSELECTED(Transactions),
        Transactions[Date] <= MAX(Transactions[Date])
    )
)
ğŸ”¹ 10. How do you handle missing values in visuals?
Answer: Use IF(ISBLANK()) logic or replace with 0 in DAX.
